Module kivakit.core.resource
Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.resource.resources.packaged

Class Package

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.telenav.kivakit.core.resource.resources.packaged.Package
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ResourceFolder
    public class Package
extends java.lang.Object
implements ResourceFolder
    An abstraction missing from the JDK for dealing with the content of packages. A package folder is constructed with a PackagePath, which specifies the location of the package. Resources in the package folder can be obtained with resources().
    Author:
    jonathanl (shibo)
    See Also:
    PackagePath, PackageResource
